	</div>
	<div align="center" class="main-content">
		<div class="spacer">
	</div><br>			<label class="collapse_ACT" for="_1"><font size="5px">RcsB transcriptional activity</font></label>
				<input id="_1" type="checkbox">
				<div class="ACT"><br><ul><li>RcsB represses SPI1 through HilD ( Mouslim et al. , 2004 ; Lin et al. , 2008 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25972862" target="_blank">25972862</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB can bind to DNA as a homodimer , moter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19126546" target="_blank">19126546</a>]<br></li>
<li>Phosphorylated RcsB binds DNA as a heterodimer with RcsA or an unknown partner or as a homodimer to activate transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17010160" target="_blank">17010160</a>]<br></li>
				<label class="ACT_collapse_similarity" for="act_similarity_4">
NarL binds to its DNA targets as a homodimer , whereas RcsB can bind to DNA either as a homodimer or as a heterodimer with RcsA ( 22 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19126546" target="_blank">19126546</a>]<br></label>
<input id="act_similarity_4", type="checkbox">
<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>RcsB can bind to diverse DNA targets as either a homodimer or as a heterodimer with RcsA ( 20 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19126546" target="_blank">19126546</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>These results indicate that RcsB can regulate different processes depending on its phosphorylation status .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22582278" target="_blank">22582278</a>]<br></li>
<li>SrfJ , a Salmonella Type III Secretion System Effector Regulated by PhoP , RcsB , and IolR Mar Cordero-Alba , Joaquín Bernal-Bayard , * and Francisco Ramos-Morales Departamento de Genética , Facultad de Biología , Universidad de Sevilla , Seville , Spain Virulence-related type III secretion systems are present in many Gram-negative bacterial pathogens .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22661691" target="_blank">22661691</a>]<br></li>
				<label class="ACT_collapse_similarity" for="act_similarity_8">
SrfJ , a Sal-monella type III secretion system effector regulated by PhoP , RcsB , and IolR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=26199328" target="_blank">26199328</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25182488" target="_blank">25182488</a>]<br></label>
<input id="act_similarity_8", type="checkbox">
<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>SrfJ , a Salmonella type III secretion system effector regulated by PhoP , RcsB , and IolR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29270156" target="_blank">29270156</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23504014" target="_blank">23504014</a>]<br></li>
<li>Cordero-Alba M , Bernal-Bayard J , Ramos-Morales F ( 2012 ) SrfJ , a Salmonella type III secretion system effector regulated by PhoP , RcsB , and IolR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27999939" target="_blank">27999939</a>]<br></li>
<li>Cordero-Alba , M. , Bernal-Bayard , J. , and Ramos-Morales , F. ( 2012 ) SrfJ , a Salmonella type III secretion system effector regulated by PhoP , RcsB , and IolR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>The biofilm master regulatory gene csgD is activated by unphosphorylated RcsB , but repressed upon RcsB phosphorylation ( Latasa et al. , 2012 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>In a tolB mutant , ugd expression is enhanced by RcsB and its coregulator RcsA in a PhoP-PmrA-independent manner ( 29 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
<li>In fact , our experiments show that in addition to being repressed by RcsB , srfABC is repressed by PhoP .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17616593" target="_blank">17616593</a>]<br></li>
<li>g005 These results confirm that wzz expression is induced by RcsB and repressed by PmrA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23418573" target="_blank">23418573</a>]<br></li>
<li>In contrast , ssaV is activated by PhoP but not by RcsB , and gmm is activated by RcsB but not by PhoP ( Table 5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17616593" target="_blank">17616593</a>]<br></li>
<li>Gene targets regulated by RcsB independently from RcsA are involved in motility , virulence , survival and other physiological processes .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>A proximal promoter , PsrfJ , responds to intravacuolar signals and is positively regulated by SsrB and PhoP and negatively regulated by RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29270156" target="_blank">29270156</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of srfJ is regulated positively by SsrB and PhoP and negatively by RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22661691" target="_blank">22661691</a>]<br></li>
<li>FIG 4 srfJ is regulated by PhoP , SsrB , and RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22661691" target="_blank">22661691</a>]<br></li>
<li>Genes positively regulated by RcsB ( or negatively regulated by IgaA ) and genes negatively regulated by RcsB ( or positively regulated by IgaA ) were identiﬁed .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17616593" target="_blank">17616593</a>]<br></li>
<li>b Induction ratios were determined as follows : igaA5/igaA for genes positively regulated by RcsB ( positive values ) and igaA / igaA5 for genes negatively regulated by RcsB ( negative values ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17616593" target="_blank">17616593</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is also not clear how RcsB helps EcnR to inhibit class 1 transcription , and this interaction is labeled with a question mark .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19114490" target="_blank">19114490</a>]<br></li>
<li>The simplest explanation for these results is that unphosphorylated RcsB is required to activate CsgD expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22582278" target="_blank">22582278</a>]<br></li>
<li>Together , these results indicate that RcsB does not require active phosphorelay to induce bioﬁlm development .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22582278" target="_blank">22582278</a>]<br></li>
<li>Nevertheless , our data suggest that RcsB also contributes to dps expression during a more prolonged stationary phase , when PrcsB starts to be active .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25028458" target="_blank">25028458</a>]<br></li>
<li>S. enterica serovar Typhimurium oligonucleotide microarrays were used to identify 18 loci that are activated by RcsC , RcsD and RcsB but not RcsA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17010160" target="_blank">17010160</a>]<br></li>
<li>Based on these observations , we hypothesized that spvAB could be subjected to positive regulation by dephosphorylated RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>These include the Spi-1 encoded repressor RtsB , as well as LrhA , SlyA and RcsB ( Lehnen et al. , 2002 ; Ellermeier and Slauch , 2003 ; Wang et al. , 2007 ; Erhardt and Hughes , 2010 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ugd gene encoding UDP-glucose dehydrogenase , which enables colonic acid and lipopoly-saccharide ( LPS ) 4-aminoarabinose production , and the capsule synthesis operon cps are positively regulated under RcsB activating conditions ( Mouslim et al. , 2003 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>The unstable RcsA protein and additional auxillary proteins can also interact and regulate RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22291596" target="_blank">22291596</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsC and RcsD are periplasmic membrane proteins that heterodimerize to function as a ` modified hybrid sensor kinase ' and RcsB is a cytoplasmic response-regulator ( Takeda et al. , 2001 ; Majdalani and Gottesman , 2005 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17010160" target="_blank">17010160</a>]<br></li>
<li>When RcsF binds IgaA , RcsC and RcsD autophosphorylate and catalyze phosphotransfer to RcsA and RcsB ( 19 ) ( 20 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29735519" target="_blank">29735519</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB is reported to positively regulate SPI-2 expression and favor Salmo-nella growth in macrophages ( 23 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23873910" target="_blank">23873910</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , when RcsB ( D56Q ) was produced in wildtype and igaA1 strains , spvA expression increased up to 22 - and 90-fold , respectively ( Fig. 5B ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
				<label class="ACT_collapse_similarity" for="act_similarity_36">
We report that RcsB regulates ﬂagellar gene expression both negatively and positively .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></label>
<input id="act_similarity_36", type="checkbox">
<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>Indeed , RcsB regulates ﬂagellar gene expression both negatively and positively .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23554419" target="_blank">23554419</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>In summary , we showed that in S. Enteritidis Dam methylation regulates wzz expression through rcsB and pmrA genes ; whereas RcsB induces wzz gene expression PmrA represses it .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23418573" target="_blank">23418573</a>]<br></li>
<li>We also present evidence that rcsB and pmrA genes regulate each other ; RcsB stimulates the expression of pmrA and PmrA represses rcsB gene expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23418573" target="_blank">23418573</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB and FimZ , however , retained some capacity for negatively regulating motility .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19114490" target="_blank">19114490</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition , RcsB inhibits flhDC expression and thereby exerts a negative effect on motility [ 45 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23443158" target="_blank">23443158</a>]<br></li>
<li>In E. coli , RcsC phosphorylates a second histidine kinase , YojN , which activates the RcsB response-regulator ( Takeda et al. , 2001 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12675799" target="_blank">12675799</a>]<br></li>
				<label class="ACT_collapse_similarity" for="act_similarity_43">
The RcsC sensor kinase phosphorylates RcsD , which subsequently phopshorylates the DNA binding response-regulator RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22291596" target="_blank">22291596</a>]<br></label>
<input id="act_similarity_43", type="checkbox">
<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>The RcsC sensor kinase normally phosphorylates RcsD , which subsequently phosphorylates the DNA binding response-regulator RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22291596" target="_blank">22291596</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>These results would indicate that , under the growth conditions used , RcsB stimulates pmrA whereas PmrA represses rcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23418573" target="_blank">23418573</a>]<br></li>
<li>rcsB overexpression represses PrcsDB activity RESULTS RcsB overproduction represses rcsD transcription We have previously demonstrated that rcsB overexpression from plasmid prcsB results in strong repression of rcsD gene expression , while its own expression is not affected ( Pescaretti et al. , 2009 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20724387" target="_blank">20724387</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this assay we observed that dps gene expression was 5.6-fold increased in rcsC11 compared with wild-type levels , while in the rcsC11 rcsB double mutant expression was strongly reduced , indicating that RcsB is required for dps induction ( C. Mouslim et al. , unpublished data ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25028458" target="_blank">25028458</a>]<br></li>
<li>Some genes , such as STM1863-STM1864 or yciGFE , are downregulated when RcsB is not functional but not induced in the igaA1 mutant with a strong RcsCDB response .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
				<label class="ACT_collapse_similarity" for="act_similarity_49">
Positively regulated genes are those for which the transcription levels are elevated in an RcsB background or decreased in a rcsB background .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></label>
<input id="act_similarity_49", type="checkbox">
<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>Negatively regulated genes are those for which the transcription levels are decreased in an RcsB background or increased in a rcsB background .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li></div>
