<li>As a starting point , we measured RprA levels by Northern blotting in our genetic backgrounds which lead to different phosphorylation levels of RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22582278" target="_blank">22582278</a>]<br></li>
<li>The possibility of RcsB phosphorylation via acetyl phosphate is also shown .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22582278" target="_blank">22582278</a>]<br></li>
<li>Capsule synthesis also is reported to be activated by acetyl phosphate via RcsB independently of RcsC ( 20 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li>
<li>( b ) Effect of RcsCDB system activation on dps transcription : system activation produced by rcsC11 , tolB or other conditions leads to RcsB phosphorylation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25028458" target="_blank">25028458</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsC or RcsD catalyze phosphorylation of RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24023746" target="_blank">24023746</a>]<br></li>
<li>In contrast , the prevention of RcsB phosphorylation either by impeding phosphorelay from RcsC or RcsD or by producing a nonphosphorylatable variant of RcsB enhances bioﬁlm development .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22582278" target="_blank">22582278</a>]<br></li>
<li>Latasa , C. , Garcıa , B. , Echeverz , M. , Toledo-Arana , A. , Valle , J. , Campoy , S. , et al. ( 2012 ) Salmonella biofilm development depends on the phosphorylation status of RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>Latasa , C. ; Garcia , B. ; Echeverz , M. ; Toledo-Arana , A. ; Valle , J. ; Campoy , S. ; Garcia-del Portillo , F. ; Solano , C. ; Lasa , I. Salmonella biofilm development depends on the phosphorylation status of RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23443158" target="_blank">23443158</a>]<br></li>
<li>In Salmonella , under environmental conditions where the Rcs system is off , RcsB would be mainly unphosphorylated , and it would induce CsgD expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22582278" target="_blank">22582278</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is proposed that the mucM product interferes with RcsB activation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11425476" target="_blank">11425476</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since EnvZ is a known osmolarity sensor for SPI-2 genes [ 26 ] , it is likely that YfhA regulates T6SS activation ( through RcsB ) depending on the osmolarity sensed by EnvZ .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24079299" target="_blank">24079299</a>]<br></li>
<li>Therefore , genes regulated by RcsB are expected to be regulated by IgaA in the opposite way .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17616593" target="_blank">17616593</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , unlike wzzst , wzzfepE is not regulated by RcsB and therefore is not involved in the bacterial swarming behaviour ( result not shown ) , but it is involved in survival within macrophages and also in resistance to polymyxin B .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21719537" target="_blank">21719537</a>]<br></li>
<li>The RcsB-regulated Gmm protein is expressed in LB broth but not in murine spleen ( Domingez-Bernal et al. , 2004 ) , consistent with the notion that the RcsC/YojN/RcsB system is turned off in host tissues because its activation has deleterious effects for Salmonella virulence ( Table 1 and Fig. 1 ; Domingez-Bernal et al. , 2004 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15469511" target="_blank">15469511</a>]<br></li>
<li>Other genes , such as spvAB , display a complex regulatory pattern since they are positively regulated by RcsB ( repressed in the igaA rcsB and rcsB strains ) but also downregulated when the RcsC3RcsD3RcsB phosphorelay is stimulated ( igaA1 strain ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
