<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>It is noteworthy that when the RcsC-YojN-RcsB system is activated by iron challenge in a pmrA mutant , ugd transcription is directed by RcsB and PhoP in an RcsA-independent manner ( 30 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>The transcription ratios at elevated levels of RcsB ( wild type compared to RcsB ) show that the same genes are repressed when RcsB is highly active , i.e. , negatively regulated by RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , other interpretations are also possible , such as that spvA was activated at low RcsB P levels but repressed at high levels of RcsB P or that RcsB was phosphorylated by other phospho-donors , such as acetyl-phosphate in the rcsC or rcsD mutant .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>Whether transcription of ydeI is directly or indirectly regulated by PhoP , PmrA , and RcsB is unknown , but a putative PhoP-binding site exists 65 nucleotides upstream of the ydeI promoter ( 47 ; data not shown ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19767429" target="_blank">19767429</a>]<br></li>
<li>We also found that PhoP , but not PmrA , negatively modulates the expression of gmm , a gene required for colanic acid synthesis that is regulated positively by RcsC-YojN-RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
<li>The rcsB gene is expressed from both promoters , PrcsDB and PrcsB , producing high levels of RcsB , which is then phosphorylated and can modulate the expression of those genes that are required for adaptation ( Fig. 6 , activation state ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20724387" target="_blank">20724387</a>]<br></li>
<li>Taken together , these results indicate that nonphosphorylated RcsB is required for the expression of CsgD and that , hence , CsgD is not expressed when RcsB is deleted or when RcsB is pres-ent mainly in its phosphorylated form .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22582278" target="_blank">22582278</a>]<br></li>
<li>spvA expression is positively controlled by RcsB but affected negatively by the RcsC3RcsD3RcsB phosphorelay .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>In SsrB , a negatively charged glutamic acid res - These results demonstrate that Lys179 and Met186 are both idue replaces Lys188 of NarL , whereas in RcsB , it is replaced by a important for sseI promoter activation by SsrB , whereas Thr183 serine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19126546" target="_blank">19126546</a>]<br></li>
<li>Here we show that the srfABC operon is negatively regulated by RcsB and by PhoP .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17616593" target="_blank">17616593</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , we show that the sfrABC operon is repressed by both RcsB and PhoP , providing examples of PhoP-re-pressed genes ( prg genes ) that are simultaneously repressed by RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17616593" target="_blank">17616593</a>]<br></li>
<li>DISCUSSION We previously showed that SrfJ can be secreted through the T3SS2 of S. Typhimurium and that its expression is positively regulated by PhoP and SsrB , and negatively regulated by RcsB and IolR ( Cordero-Alba et al. , 2012 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29270156" target="_blank">29270156</a>]<br></li>
<li>More recently it has been shown that the leuO gene is activated by the transcriptional-regulators RcsB and BglJ and is negatively auto-regulated ( Stratmann et al. , 2012 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22804842" target="_blank">22804842</a>]<br></li>
<li>When activated by the RcsC component , probably through phosphorylation , RcsB acts as a positive e ¡ ector for cps transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11425476" target="_blank">11425476</a>]<br></li>
<li>After reaching a threshold concentration , RcsB protein represses rcsD transcription by binding to the PrcsDB promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20724387" target="_blank">20724387</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , as RpoS is a global sigma factor , specific transcription factors , such as RcsB , may determine the activation of specific genes under certain conditions ( Hengge-Aronis , 2002 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17010160" target="_blank">17010160</a>]<br></li>
<li>The RcsB response-regulator can form functional homodimers , however , its activity can be enhanced by the formation of heterodimers with auxiliary proteins ( Pristovsek et al. , 2003 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>Interestingly , RcsA can form heterodimers with the response-regulator RcsB , which activates leuO transcription in conjunction with BglJ , counteracting H-NS repression of leuO transcription ( Stratmann et al. , 2012 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22804842" target="_blank">22804842</a>]<br></li>
<li>Interestingly , in S. Typhimurium , RcsB regulates flhDC transcription independent of the auxiliary protein RcsA ( Cano et al. , 2002 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>For instance , PhoP also activates transcription from the ugd promoter in a manner dependent on the response-regulator RcsB ( Mouslim et al. , 2003 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22435712" target="_blank">22435712</a>]<br></li>
<li>This feature of the RcsC-YojN-RcsB regulatory system may certainly necessitate spe-ciﬁc negative regulators , such as IgaA , dedicated to prevent either high intensity or prolonged manifestation of the response ( Gottesman , 1995 ; Conter et al. , 2002 ; Sailer et al. , 2003 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15387821" target="_blank">15387821</a>]<br></li>
<li>Phosphorylated RcsB activates target genes of the Rcs regulon ( Takeda et al. , 2001 ; Majdalani and Gottesman , 2005 ; Huang et al. , 2006 ) ( Fig. 5.3 b ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20593264" target="_blank">20593264</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB activates transcription of genes involved in physiological processes like the wzzst gene responsible for correct LPS O-antigen formation and the dps gene involved in oxidative-stress resistance ( Delgado et al. , 2006 ; Farizano et al. , 2014 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>For example , the RcsC -- YojN -- RcsB system of E. coli is activated in cells that overproduce the DnaJ-like protein DjlA from E. coli ( Clarke et al. , 1997 ; Kelley and Georgopoulos , 1997 ) or Coxiella burnetti ( Zuber et al. , 1995 ) , and this is apparently the result of breaches in outer membrane permeability because DjlA overproduction increases bacterial sensitivity to EDTA and novobiocin ( Bernard et al. , 1998 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12519186" target="_blank">12519186</a>]<br></li>
<li>In Escherichia coli , the RcsC/YojN/RcsB system can be activated by a variety of conditions including desiccation , growth on a solid surface and osmotic shock , by treatment with the cationic amphipatic compound chloprozamine ( Gottesman et al. , 1985 ; Conter et al. , 2002 ; Ferrieres and Clarke , 2003 ) , as well as upon overproduction of the genes encoding the cell surface proteins DjlA , LolA or OmpG and by mutation of the mdoH gene , which alters the bacterial cell envelope ( Ebel et al. , 1997 ; Kelley and Georgopoulos , 1997 ; Carballes et al. , 1999 ; Chen et al. , 2001 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15469511" target="_blank">15469511</a>]<br></li>
<li>Upon activation of the Rcs system , RcsB cooperates with the transcription factor RcsA to express the cps genes required for colonic acid capsule biosynthesis in S. Typhimurium or with TviA to promote Vi antigen production in S. Typhi ( Gottesman et al. , 1985 ; Mouslim et al. , 2003 ; Erickson and Detweiler , 2006 ; Huang et al. , 2006 ; Winter et al. , 2009 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20593264" target="_blank">20593264</a>]<br></li>
<li>In contrast , activated RcsB inhibits transcription of genes belonging to the Spi-1 regulon , as well as the Spi-2 effector-molecule srfJ and constitutive activation of the Rcs system results in attenuation of virulence ( Mouslim et al. , 2004 ; Garcıa-Calderon et al. , 2005 , 2007 ; Lin et al. , 2008 ; Cordero-Alba et al. , 2012 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of rflM was analyzed in a strain that constitutively expressed flhDC from PtetA to prevent any indirect effect of RcsB via flhDC repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>We detected increased fluorescence of 50-Cy5-labeled flhDC promoter DNA with increasing concentrations of RcsB or His6-SUMO-RflM / RcsB complex due to enhancement of fluorescence intensity after DNA-binding ( Fig. 7 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>MviA regulation of RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19218385" target="_blank">19218385</a>]<br></li>
<li>S6C , increasing levels of rflM decreased expression of flhC-lac , providing further evidence for a cooperative action of RflM and RcsB in repression of flhDC .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>We dem-onstrate that RflM functions as a novel co-regulator of RcsB and mediates target specificity of unphosphoryl-ated RcsB for repression of flhDC .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>RflM , however , did not repress flhDC transcription in the absence of RcsB protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the absence of environmental signals , phosphorylation of RcsB does not occur .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>A. DNaseI footprint analysis of 50-DIG-labeled P1flhDC promoter fragment in the presence of increasing amounts of purified His6-SUMO-RflM/RcsB complex .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>Overexpressed RcsB or a phosphomimetic RcsBD56E mutant were able to repress flhDC , but RcsB-mediated repression of flhDC increased significantly in the presence of RflM .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>As mentioned , we found that phosphorylation of RcsB was not essential for repression of flhDC in the presence of RflM , but for RcsB-mediated repression of flhDC in the absence of RflM .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>We propose that RflM stabilizes binding of unphosphorylated RcsB to the flhDC promoter in absence of environmental cues .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>The lack of selfdimerization could be due to the absence of target DNA or phosphorylation of RcsB that presumably would facilitate RcsB dimer formation in the absence of RflM .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>Curiously , RcsB selectively stimulates expression of the ﬂagellar type 3 secretion genes ﬂiPQR ; an RcsAB box located downstream of ﬂiR inﬂuences this regulation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li>
<li>Auxiliary proteins of RcsB allow additional signal input by altering the activity of this response-regulator ( reviewed in ( Majdalani & Gottesman , 2005 ) ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>Identiﬁcation of promoters that are directly regulated by RcsB will allow a dissection of the molecular mechanism of this regulation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li>
<li>Repression of PsrfJ by RcsB correlates with previous reports suggesting that high level of activation of the system negatively regulates expression of SPI1 and SPI2 genes ( Wang et al. , 2007 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29270156" target="_blank">29270156</a>]<br></li>
<li>The microarray data revealed a third class of genes that were bot positively and negatively regulated depending of the activity level of RcsB ( Table 2 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li>
<li>Bouchart F , Boussemart G , Prouvost A-F , Cogez V , Madec E , Vidal O , Delrue B , Bohin J-P , Lacroix J-M ( 2010 ) The virulence of a Dickeya dadantii 3937 mutant devoid of osmoregulated periplasmic glucans is restored by inactivation of the RcsCD-RcsB phosphorelay .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=28593349" target="_blank">28593349</a>]<br></li>
<li>It thus represents the indicator me-dium of choice to visualize repression of ﬂhDC , such as ﬂhDC autorepression ( ParaﬂhD C ) or repression of ﬂhDC by the known transcriptional-regulator RcsB ( PararcsB ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23873910" target="_blank">23873910</a>]<br></li>
<li>A. Schematic regulatory model of repression of the flagellar master regulator flhDC by coordinated action of RcsB and RflM .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>The FlhD4C2-dependent RflM protein thus enables Salmonella to fine-tune expression levels of the motility master regulator during early stages of flagellar synthesis by sequestering RcsB protein for repression of flagellar synthesis independent on the presence of external stimuli .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since RflM in the absence of RcsB was unstable and was not successfully purified alone , we co-purified His6-SUMO-RflM/RcsB complex .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>We thus propose that RflM modulates binding affinity of RcsB for its target DNA and enables a fast and stable binding of a RcsB-RflM heterodimer to the flhDC promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>RflM interacts with RcsB and forms a heterodimer that binds to the RcsB/RflM box of flhDC with high affinity to repress flhDC transcription after the initial surge of flhDC expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB-RflM complex coordinately represses flhDC transcription We hypothesized that the interaction of RflM with RcsB could promote specificity of RcsB to its target DNA by formation of a stable RcsB-RflM protein complex that is able to efficiently repress flhDC transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results indicated that RflM directs RcsB to specifically repress flhDC gene transcription independently of external stimuli that would result in RcsB phosphorylation , similar to the mode of action of other RcsB co-regulator complexes such as BglJ-RcsB ( Venkatesh et al. , 2010 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>Salmonella RcsA is an auxiliary protein , which sometimes acts in concert with RcsB to regulate a distinct subset of the RcsB regulon ( Mouslim et al. , 2003 ; Erickson and Detweiler , 2006 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27558204" target="_blank">27558204</a>]<br></li>
<li>TviA activates its own transcription and is thought to serve as an auxiliary protein for RcsB ( Virlogeux et al. , 1996 , Majdalani & Gottesman , 2005 ) , the response-regulator of the RcsC/RcsD/RcsB phosphorelay system .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of ftsA1p , the ftsA-ftsZ promoter submitted to RcsB stimulation , is greatly increased in mucM mutants , and this expression is dependent on RcsB and ftsA1p .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11425476" target="_blank">11425476</a>]<br></li>
<li>ensable for in vivo survival and in vitro AMP resistance p is d is A cs R RcsB can form a heterodimer with the transcription factor RcsA , and RcsB/RcsA heterodimers bind to the RcsAB DNA box within promoters to activate or repress transcription ( Wehland and Bernhard , 2000 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17010160" target="_blank">17010160</a>]<br></li>
<li>Under these conditions , TviA is available as a co-repressor for RcsB , resulting in reduced invasion gene and flagellar gene expression and activation of genes in the viaB locus , resulting in capsule ( Vi antigen ) production .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20808848" target="_blank">20808848</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition , at low osmolarity , RcsB , acting in association with TviA , negatively controls the transcription of flhDC , which is apparently required for activation of iagA ( hilA ) , invF and sipB ( encoding proteins involved in cell invasion ) [ 25 , 34 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19745516" target="_blank">19745516</a>]<br></li>
<li>Interestingly FlhD and FlhC , which are negatively regulated by RcsB , have been shown to regulate a number of E. coli genes involved in anaerobic respiration ( 71 ) , but dcuB and narH were not on the list .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17616593" target="_blank">17616593</a>]<br></li>
<li>The positive regulation of these ﬂagellar ex-port-related genes by RcsB , for which other positively regulated functions are involved in responding to membrane stress , including capsule and other polysaccharide synthesis , suggests that perhaps FliPQR have a dual role in the cell .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li>
<li>A majority of the genes showing dual regulation by RcsB in our studies , i.e. , genes positively regulated at normal levels and negatively regulated at highly activated levels of RcsB , either belong to the SPI-2 group or are virulence determinants known to be involved in survival in macrophages , which are endowed with robust and varied antimicrobial defenses ( 55 ) ( Table 2 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li>
<li>Three of the genes activated by RcsB independently of RcsA are ugd , ftsZ ( Majdalani and Gottesman , 2005 ) and ydeI , as shown in this article .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17010160" target="_blank">17010160</a>]<br></li>
<li>Three two-component systems are involved in its regulation ( PmrAB , PhoPQ and RcsCB ) [ 12,15 ] and this is reflected in the presence of the corresponding motifs : ugd contains PmrA , PhoP and RcsB motifs .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14759259" target="_blank">14759259</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsA enhances RcsB-dependent capsule synthesis by binding together with RcsB to the RcsAB box of target genes ( Majdalani and Gottesman , 2005 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>A positive regulator , TviA ( VipR ) , activates its own synthesis by binding upstream of the tviA promoter [ 27 ] and interacts with RcsB to promote optimal transcription of genes involved in Vi antigen synthesis [ 24 , 25 , 28 , 29 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19745516" target="_blank">19745516</a>]<br></li>
<li>The RcsB and RcsC regulatory system of Salmonella typhi differentially regulates the expression of invasion proteins , ﬂagellin and Vi antigen in response to osmolarity .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12480883" target="_blank">12480883</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB , which regulates capsular polysaccharide synthesis and a number of genes in response to membrane and cell wall damage , is a known repressor of ﬂhDC transcription ( 23 , 24 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24706743" target="_blank">24706743</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since IgaA prevents activation of the RcsC-YojN-RcsB phosphorelay and since this system regulates ugd , we were interested in deciphering a probable regulatory link between IgaA and PhoP-PhoQ .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
<li>Therefore , MucM could in # uence the sensor activity of RcsC either by altering the conditions sensed by RcsC , as dsbB and certain LPS mutations are supposed to do , or directly by a ¡ ecting RcsC interaction with RcsB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11425476" target="_blank">11425476</a>]<br></li>
<li>pmrE can be activated in vitro by PhoP , PmrA and RcsB ( RcsC -- YojB -- RcsB phosphorelay ) , all of which can bind to the pmrE promoter directly [ 60 -- 62 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18467098" target="_blank">18467098</a>]<br></li>
<li>Note that the increased ugd transcription by the igaA1 mutant was promoted by functional RcsC , RcsB , and RcsA proteins , whereas it was independent of PhoP and PmrA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of srfJ is positively regulated by the two-component systems PhoP/PhoQ and SsrA/SsrB and negatively regulated by the RcsC/RcsD/RcsB phosphorelay system .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22661691" target="_blank">22661691</a>]<br></li>
<li>This partial inhibition by RcsB and FimZ might be an indirect effect through the upregulation of capsule and ﬁmbrial synthesis .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19114490" target="_blank">19114490</a>]<br></li>
<li>To confirm that PrcsDB alone is repressed by high levels of RcsB and to simultaneously discount any polar effect , the PrcsDB and PrcsB activities were determined as GFP production .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20724387" target="_blank">20724387</a>]<br></li>
<li>This positive regulatory circuit was noticeable only upon activation of the RcsC-YojN-RcsB phosphorelay .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
<li>This negative regulatory circuit controlled by IgaA is crucial for infection since activation of the RcsC-YojN-RcsB phosphorelay attenuates virulence ( 12 , 28 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
