<li>Complex regulation by two-component systems 337 the tolB mutation induced cps expression , and this induction was dependent on the RcsC -- YojN -- RcsB phosphorelay and the RcsA protein because no expression was observed in tolB rcsA and tolB rcsB mutants ( Fig. 3B ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12519186" target="_blank">12519186</a>]<br></li>
<li>We observed similar expression patterns when the cps or flhDC expressions were induced by RcsB overproduction and acetyl phosphate accumulation , but in this last condition the levels were higher than when only rcsB was overexpressed ( Fig. 1 and 2 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24023746" target="_blank">24023746</a>]<br></li>
<li>Under these conditions , the ugd gene , included in the cps regulon belonging to the RcsC-YojN-RcsB regulon , is positively regulated by PhoP via PmrA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
<li>This activation is mediated by the RcsC -- YojN -- RcsB phosphorelay and the RcsA protein , suggesting a role for ugd in capsule synthesis .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12519186" target="_blank">12519186</a>]<br></li>
<li>We next examined whether the increased ugd transcription linked to the igaA1 mutation could be altered by defects in the regulatory and/or sensor proteins PhoP , PmrA , RcsA , RcsB , and RcsC .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is noteworthy that a different regulation pattern was observed when the ﬁndings were compared to the ﬁndings for ugd ; the pag genes mgtA and pgbP are modulated negatively by the RcsB protein in an RcsA-independent manner .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although the data in Fig. 4 suggest that RcsCDB and FliZ independently affect SPI1 expression in the dsbA mutant , this interpretation is complicated by the fact that RcsB and cofactor RcsA can negatively regulate the ﬂagellar regulon ( including FliZ ) by binding directly to the ﬂhDC promoter region ( 21 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17951383" target="_blank">17951383</a>]<br></li>
<li>Furthermore as the auxillary protein RcsA can interact and regulate RcsB , we therefore disrupted the rcsA gene in DmreC and which also resulted in no impact on the observed phenotypes ( Figure 5 , S6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22291596" target="_blank">22291596</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition to the RcsB overproduction reported , rcsD repression also occurs in the rcsC11 mutant and even more so under a physiological condition such as polymyxin B treatment .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20724387" target="_blank">20724387</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition to the three mentioned above Hfq negatively modulates PhoB involved in the phosphate-starvation response , RstA , NarP , RcsB , BasR , and CpxR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19277208" target="_blank">19277208</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the absence of TviA , RcsB repressed flhC expression by approximately 2-fold , however this repression was osmolarity-independent ( Fig. 8B ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
