<li>Indeed , RcsB regulates ﬂagellar gene expression both negatively and positively .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23554419" target="_blank">23554419</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>Thus , low-level RcsB turned cps expression on in yrfFþ rcsC and yrfFþ yojN mutants but not in yrfFþ rcsB strains .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12757942" target="_blank">12757942</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is noteworthy that spvA expression was found to be normal in rscC and rcsD mutants , which indicated that an intact RcsC3RcsD3RcsB phosphorelay was not required for this regulation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB ( D56Q ) causes a more-pronounced positive effect on spvA when it is produced in an rcsB background , which suggests that both RcsB P and dephosphorylated RcsB may be required for attaining proper spvA expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , when RcsB ( D56Q ) was produced in wildtype and igaA1 strains , spvA expression increased up to 22 - and 90-fold , respectively ( Fig. 5B ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB is reported to positively regulate SPI-2 expression and favor Salmo-nella growth in macrophages ( 23 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23873910" target="_blank">23873910</a>]<br></li>
<li>The RcsA and RcsB proteins have been shown to bind to this box and to positively regulate rcsA expression in E. coli ( 70 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li>
