<div class="TU_similar">
<li>Negatively regulated genes are those for which the transcription levels are decreased in an RcsB background or increased in a rcsB background .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17905992" target="_blank">17905992</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>Genes regulated by RcsB independently of RcsA include ftsZ , osmC , and rprA ( 20 -- 22 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=28588134" target="_blank">28588134</a>]<br></li>
<li>Coordinated repression of flhDC transcription by RcsB and RflM .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>Similarly , repression of hilA by RcsB was dependent on flhDC ( Fig. 3B ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>In Salmonella and E. coli , RcsB induces expression of genes involved in capsular polysaccharide synthesis , responses to oxidative stress , resistance to antimicrobial peptides and systemic colonization of mice ( Gottesman et al. , 1985 ; Erickson and Detweiler , 2006 ; Clarke , 2010 ; Farizano et al. , 2014 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27558204" target="_blank">27558204</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB and TviA significantly ( P < 0.05 ) repressed expression of hilA ( Fig. 3B and Fig 6A ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>Some RcsB-regulated genes , yciGFE and STM1862 ( pagO ) - STM1863-STM1864 , were equally expressed in wild-type and igaA strains , suggesting a maximal expression at low levels of RcsB P .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of genes involved in carbohydrate anabolism ( glgA , glgC and glgX ) and genes encoding an arginine deiminase system were positively regulated by RcsB and TviA ( Fig. 1 , cluster 5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>RcsB is known to repress transcription of ﬂhDC in both E. coli ( 50 ) and S. enterica ( 19 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27601571" target="_blank">27601571</a>]<br></li>
<li>An rcsC constitutive mutant exhibits decreased transcription of invasion genes including hilA , invF , sipC , and invG in a process that is RcsB dependent ( 50 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17951383" target="_blank">17951383</a>]<br></li>
<li>We also present evidence that rcsB and pmrA genes regulate each other ; RcsB stimulates the expression of pmrA and PmrA represses rcsB gene expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23418573" target="_blank">23418573</a>]<br></li>
<li>Gene expression profiling indicated that both TviA and RcsB were required for repression of flagellin and invasion gene expression in S. Typhi .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>Supporting this hypothesis , we demonstrated that the expression of both cps and flhDC operons were modulated under high RcsB levels in an rcsC or rcsD mutant .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24023746" target="_blank">24023746</a>]<br></li>
<li>Note that spvA expression is repressed in strains with high activity of the RcsC3RcsD3RcsB phosphorelay ( igaA1 mutant , igaA1 rcsA mutant , and MD0855-J10 ) and in those lacking RcsB ( igaA1 rcsB and rcsB mutants ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this sense , our micro-array results showed that RcsB induces transcription of dps in an RcsA-independent pathway , because gene expression was not affected in the rcsC11 rcsA mutant relative to those levels observed in rcsC11 ( C. Mouslim et al. , unpublished data ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25028458" target="_blank">25028458</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both RcsB and TviA repressed expression of flhDC , but only TviA altered flhDC expression in response to osmolarity .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>Osmoregulation of flhDC expression in S. Typhi was mediated through RcsB in conjunction with TviA , but not through RcsB alone .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19703107" target="_blank">19703107</a>]<br></li>
<li>Intriguingly , RcsB has been shown previously to regulate genes in the std operon ( 52 ) , further suggesting that RtsB regulates this operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27601571" target="_blank">27601571</a>]<br></li>
<li>The data obtained with the nonphosphorylatable RcsB ( D56Q ) variant demonstrated that RcsB does not need to be phosphorylated to promote spvA expression ( Fig. 5B ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both the Psp ( 1 ) and RcsB ( 68 ) responses are induced during stationary phase .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=28588134" target="_blank">28588134</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ugd promoter has binding sites for the PmrA , PhoP and RcsB proteins , and the latter two proteins are necessary to promote ugd transcription under certain inducing conditions ( Mouslim and Groisman , 2003 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22435712" target="_blank">22435712</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ugd gene encoding UDP-glucose dehydrogenase , which enables colonic acid and lipopoly-saccharide ( LPS ) 4-aminoarabinose production , and the capsule synthesis operon cps are positively regulated under RcsB activating conditions ( Mouslim et al. , 2003 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>In Salmonella , under environmental conditions where the Rcs system is off , RcsB would be mainly unphosphorylated , and it would induce CsgD expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22582278" target="_blank">22582278</a>]<br></li>
<li>Other genes , such as spvAB , display a complex regulatory pattern since they are positively regulated by RcsB ( repressed in the igaA rcsB and rcsB strains ) but also downregulated when the RcsC3RcsD3RcsB phosphorelay is stimulated ( igaA1 strain ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19124574" target="_blank">19124574</a>]<br></li>
<li>Besides genes that are also found in the Escherichia coli genome , our screens identiﬁed Salmonella-speciﬁc genes regulated by RcsB , including bapA , siiE , srfA , and srfB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17616593" target="_blank">17616593</a>]<br></li>
<li>Note that the increased ugd transcription by the igaA1 mutant was promoted by functional RcsC , RcsB , and RcsA proteins , whereas it was independent of PhoP and PmrA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
<li>Decrease in mgtA and pbgP transcription observed in the igaA1 mutant is promoted by RcsB via RpoS and is independent of RcsA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></li>
				<label class="TU_collapse_similarity" for="tu_similarity_55">
However , when the RcsC-YojN-RcsB system is activated by the presence of iron in a pmrA mutant , ugd expression is promoted by both RcsB and PhoP regulators in an RcsA-independent manner ( 30 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516559" target="_blank">15516559</a>]<br></label>
